OL,3,CBirmingham bin workers being balloted
OL,4,Cfor strike action
OL,6,FFrank Keogh, Unite regional
OL,7,Fcoordinating officer, said:
OL,8,F"Birmingham council is deliberately
OL,9,Fplaying fast and loose with the safety
OL,10,Fof workers and the general public.
OL,12,F"Birmingham's refuse workers are done
OL,13,Fbeing scapegoats for a crisis created
OL,14,Fby politicians.
OL,16,F"They've already sacrificed plenty to
OL,17,Fkeep services running while facing
OL,18,Frelentless attacks on their jobs.
OL,19,FAxing the WRCO role is seen as just
OL,20,Fthe first step in a broader attack on
OL,21,Ftheir pay, terms, and conditions."
